# Development Conventions

## General

- All code, comments, and console output must be written in English.
- Never use emojis in source code, comments, or console logs.
- Create documentation only when necessary; store all docs in `obsidian/`.
- Prefer editing existing files over creating new ones.

## Code style

- Keep functions focused and small.
- Avoid redundant comments that merely restate what the code does.
- Comments should only explain non-obvious intent, trade-offs, or constraints.

## Commit messages

- Use the imperative mood: "Add feature", "Fix bug", "Refactor module".
- Keep the subject line under 72 characters.
- Reference the relevant backlog item or decision when applicable.
